def: Capable of being condensed; as, a gas condensible to a liquidby cold.
Lying under or beneath; hence, fundamental; as, the underlyingstrata of a locality; underlying principles.
A dish made of portions of the head, or head and feet, ofswine, cut up fine, seasoned, and pressed into a cheeselike mass.
A mineral occurring in small yellow crystals, found in thelavas (melilite basalt) of Vesuvius, and elsewhere. [Written alsomellilite.]
A genus including numerous species of shells resembling Neritain form. They mostly inhabit brackish water, and are often delicatelytinted.
Having a head like that of a bull. Fig.: Headstrong; obstinate;dogged.
One of the middle parts in music, between the tenor and thetreble; high tenor. Counter-tenor clef (Mus.), the C clef when placedon the third line; -- also called alto clef.
